{"bookId": "67656cf0a790fd9b172cf0d2","moduleId": "67656cf0a790fd9b172cf0d2","subjectId": "67656cf8a790fd9b172cf0d3","chapterId": "67656cf8a790fd9b172cf0d7","subject": "Physics","chapter": "Miscellaneous Physics","count": 8,"questions": [{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Miscellaneous Physics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "The electric field in an electromagnetic wave is given by<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>50</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#969;</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mi>c</mi></mfrac><mo>)</mo></math><br />The energy contained in a cylinder of volume <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi><mo>.</mo></math>&nbsp;The value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi></math> is _______&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>.</mo></math><br />(given <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>&#1013;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>)","options": ["A","B","C","D"],"answer": 0,"solution": "Energy density <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math><br />Energy <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo></math> volume<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>50</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>500</mn><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></msup></math>","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a6b417cc3fb48d67694","paperSource": "JEE Main 2021 (31 Aug Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Miscellaneous Physics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "In a screw gauge, there are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn></math> divisions on the circular scale and the main scale moves by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math> on a complete rotation of the circular scale. The zero of circular scale lies <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math> divisions below the line of graduation when two studs are brought in contact with each other. When a wire is placed between the studs, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math> linear scale divisions are clearly visible while 46<sup>th</sup> division the circular scale coincide with the reference line. The diameter of the wire is ______&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>.</mo></math>","options": ["A","B","C","D"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<p>Least count of screw gauge is<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>Pitch</mi><mrow><mi>No</mi><mo>.</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>of</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>circular</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>divisions</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></mrow><mn>100</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Least count,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p>The zero of circular scale lies <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;divisions below the line of graduation. So, zero error is positive.</p><p>Positive zero error&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>L</mi><mi>C</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Diameter of wire,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>L</mi><mi>C</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&#8211;</mo><mi>Positive</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>zero</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>error</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>46</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>40</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p>Hence, diameter of wire is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>220</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>.</p>","difficulty": "Easy","source": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a6f417cc3fb48d681d7","paperSource": "JEE Main 2023 (30 Jan Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Miscellaneous Physics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "Both the diodes used in the circuit shown are assumed to be ideal and have negligible resistance when these are forward biased. Built in potential in each diode is <math><mn>0.7</mn><mi></mi><mi>V</mi></math>. For the input voltages shown in the figure, the voltage (in Volts) at point A is ________<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/41edeab1-5373-435f-afff-bd8219540e21-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 155px;\" />","options": ["A","B","C","D"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/63a648da-0b22-4080-a038-f0c40c19cca7-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 146px;\" /><br />Let <math><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math><br />Right diode is reversed baised and left diode is forward biased<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>12.7</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0.7</mn></math><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math> Volt","difficulty": "Easy","source": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a69417cc3fb48d66d8d","paperSource": "JEE Main 2020 (09 Jan Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Miscellaneous Physics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "In a metre bridge experiment the balance point is obtained if the gaps are closed by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#937;</mi></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#937;</mi></math>. A shunt of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#937;</mi></math> is added to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#937;</mi></math> resistor to shift the balancing point by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>22</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>. The value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi></math> is ______.","options": ["A","B","C","D"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8f974d0e-47ac-4517-bf29-f04a0ec70601-9894943.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 236px;\" /></p><p>Case&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>: No shunt is added</p><p>The initial balancing length&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi></math>&nbsp;of the bridge is,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>l</mi><mrow><mn>100</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>200</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>l</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8d24fb54-2353-4c7f-b4af-645d94bc9553-100487e4-2884-4aa2-9745-521f16f132a6-9894943_2.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 257px;\" /></p><p>Case&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>: When shunt is added</p><p>The new balancing length is,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>l</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>22</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>40</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>62</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p>So,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>62</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>37</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>X</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>X</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p>","difficulty": "Hard","source": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a6f417cc3fb48d6811f","paperSource": "JEE Main 2023 (29 Jan Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Miscellaneous Physics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "<p>Student <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and student <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> used two screw gauges of equal pitch and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn></math> equal circular divisions to measure the radius of a given wire. The actual value of the radius of the wire is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>322</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>. The absolute value of the difference between the final circular scale readings observed by the students <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> is _______.</p><p>[Figure shows position of reference <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>O</mi></math>&nbsp;when jaws of screw gauge are closed]</p><p>Given pitch <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/fc084239-971b-4b08-9eb4-762feffb4daa-image.png\" style=\"width: 349px; height: 204px;\" /></p>","options": ["A","B","C","D"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<p>For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>,</p><p>Reading <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>Error</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>322</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>300</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>L</mi><mi>C</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>322</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>300</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>005</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>017</mn></math></p><p>For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>,&nbsp;</p><p>Reading <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>Error</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>322</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>200</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>092</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>030</mn></math></p><p>Difference <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>030</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>017</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>013</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p>Division on circular scale <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>013</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>001</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>13</mn></math></p>","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a6a417cc3fb48d67310","paperSource": "JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Miscellaneous Physics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "<p>In the logic circuit shown in the figure, if input <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> respectively, the output at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Y</mi></math> would be <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>. The value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> is _________.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/46e9c281-3b90-4d58-8f65-38a9f4e7304c-image.png\" style=\"width: 369px; height: 116px;\" /></p>","options": ["A","B","C","D"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d3e1f06e-0012-4a05-aa16-90ab28de3bc1-image.png\" style=\"width: 369px; height: 142px;\" />","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a69417cc3fb48d66e83","paperSource": "JEE Main 2021 (16 Mar Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Miscellaneous Physics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "<p>For the forward biased diode characteristics shown in the figure, the dynamic resistance at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mi>D</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mA</mi></math>&nbsp;will be ________<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#937;</mi><mo>.</mo></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e1fcf718-3c47-468d-893f-3e71e7965e5f-image.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 306px;\" /></p>","options": ["A","B","C","D"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>R</mi><mi>d</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>i</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>65</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>100</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#937;</mi></math></p>","difficulty": "Easy","source": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a6a417cc3fb48d670f7","paperSource": "JEE Main 2021 (20 Jul Shift 2)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Miscellaneous Physics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "<p>In the circuit shown below, maximum Zener diode current will be _____&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>mA</mi></math>.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8442604a-603c-487b-8d83-64ed57722a78-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 126px;\" /></p>","options": ["A","B","C","D"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<blockquote><p><meta charset=\"utf-8\" /><meta charset=\"utf-8\" /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3842b7f0-258b-4c55-87b8-6a30988fe1aa-image.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 143px;\" /><b>​​​​​​​</b></p><p>Current through load resistor is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mi>L</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>60</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>10000</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&Omega;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>006</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>&nbsp;and current through&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4000</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&Omega;</mi></math>&nbsp;resistor is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mn>120</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>60</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4000</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&Omega;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>015</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></p><p>Thus, maximum current through Zener diode is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mi>Z</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>I</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>I</mi><mi>L</mi></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>015</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>006</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>009</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>mA</mi></math></p></blockquote>","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a6c417cc3fb48d6796c","paperSource": "JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 1)"}]}